Reasoning: The paper discusses the unconventional computing and sensing capabilities of live slime mould \emph{Physarum polycephalum}. The paper covers a wide range of topics including computational geometry, experimental archeology, self-routing wires, memristors, shortest path approximation, and physical models of space exploration. These topics are relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including cs.ET (Emerging Technologies), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.RO (Robotics).
